author: Hank Domin | hdomin@syracuse.com
title: Report: EJ Manuel will start at quarterback for Buffalo Bills on Sunday
text:
EJ Manuel reportedly will start at quarterback for the Buffalo Bills against the Cincinnati Bengals on Sunday.
ESPN's Bob Holtzman says that Tyrod Taylor "tried to convince coaches" that he could play.
Sources: EJ Manuel expected to start for @buffalobills tomorrow vs Bengals. Tyrod Taylor (knee) tried to convince coaches, but not ready.
— bob holtzman (@BobHoltzmanESPN) October 17, 2015 Taylor has been listed as questionable with a knee injury.
Manuel, a first-round pick in 2013, will be making his first start since week 4 of last season. He took the majority of the first-team snaps in practice this week.
The Bills (3-2) face the undefeated Bengals (5-0) at Ralph Wilson Stadium at 1 p.m. Sunday.
» Related: Is Manuel ready to step in?
